					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-797929#post-1986808</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-797929/scp-2036#post-1986808</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 08 Mar 2014 20:18:20 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1361261</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>As I mentioned in the chat, I don't really have any issues style-wise, but I feel like this is merely an above-averagely detailed Monster Manual entry. The note at the end is an attempt to counteract that, however it's managed to pack in an asston of cliches in a small space (&quot;Foundation found this for some completely ridiculous reason&quot;, &quot;vanished spooky creator leaves threatening note explaining his anomaly&quot;, &quot;note pinned threateningly to the wall in threatening manner&quot;, etc.) without giving us anything of any real substance.</p> <p>It's not terrible, and it probably would have flown in the early days of the site, but I need something more from an article in today's environment. -1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
